cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning algorithms for the detection of malignancy in medical images. Specifically, it focuses on Confocal Laser Endomicroscopy (CLE) images from different anatomical locations of the upper gastrointestinal tract. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical analysis (cs.MS) and image processing (cs.MM) techniques.
